<br>
Im somewhat new to this game and my little wizard turned 16 last night and i decided i should try out some researching.<br>
Having tried some smithing with another char and reading up on researching here i decided to try to go for practice runes first to get my skill up.<br>
Nothing had me prepared for this though...<br>
<br>
First i put my obligatory point in the skill to get it started, then i set out gathering 'ingredients' for the first practice rune.<br>
Bat wings and chips etc for the azia was easy cause i could buy whole stacks from a shop, rusty slashers for the beza took several hours though since i decided to get a little xp while gathering them.<br>
Well to get to the point, after several hours i had managed to make runes out of all the stones i had bought(full stack each)<br>
and then turned those into complete runes. This without a single skill increase, with 150int, whats up with this junk! i thought, perhaps the first one is buged. So i went to my guild to raise the skill for five more points, thus putting me at 21 since the first shouldv gotten me to my lvl of 16, and ready to with the second practice rune instead.<br>
<br>
But lo and behold, he said my skill was already maxed for my lvl! wt...<br>
<br>
<br>
Was this suposed to have been obvious or something?<br>
I have never even heard of a skill with this kind of low max setting, and since from what ive seen it should max at 200ish at lvl50 like everything else it just doesn't make any sense to me...<br>
<br>
This makes me realise that although i've seen several laydowns of what runes go to what spells etc and how to get the parts for the practicing, I haven't actually seen a single comment as to how to actually go about managing/raising the skill.<br>
<br>
Would really appreciate it if someone could give me some happy advice to what to do here!?!<br>
Was quite depressed after having put in all that time(n plat) and not get a single skillful, but that was nothing to what i became when i realised that the reason was that i COULDNT get any! =( <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urombusmindspire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/01 11:26:59 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://wots-signatures.hypermart.net/rombus/sidepic.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: what's up with research?</span><hr size=1> Research is a skill that takes a lot of practice, and patience.  It doesn't go up quick unless you're using actual runes / lexicon to practice I've found.  <br>
