<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usenien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/7/01 11:18:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: what's up with research?</span><hr size=1> At level 16 the max research skill is 1 i do believe. you have to level a lil bit more to be able to increase your skill in it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvortextwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VortexTwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/7/01 12:55:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: what's up with research?</span><hr size=1> Putting a point in research at 16 you can't get another point in research till you're level 19. <br>
<br>
Research skill is defined as (level - 15) * 5  ... and with your first point you get 16 in the skill. So at level 19 you can start to increase the skill.<br>
<br>
Its a pain to increase. I just put 5 skill points in it each level until I could research level 49 spells with ease. (it gets much more pricy at higher levels, but still cheaper than wasting time with practice runes, IMO). <p><p align="center"><img src="http://www.bigjaco.com/SG/eq_screenies/vort_sig53.jpg"></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/7/01 5:20:38 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimtoo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: what's up with research?</span><hr size=1> If you are in a guild that's friendly enough, have people save runes.  You can port, meet them at the bank when they are in town and you'll soon have to have a rune mule.  Start combining them spells, sparky, the best way to train is to make lots o' spells.  You can even sell some of them to players (level 34 AEs, for example), I always charged level in plat for the spell.  If they are junk research (Enstill) they still sell for a few plat to the vendors.  Either way you end up on top since the runes cost you nothing.  After a while that research skill really turns into a plat sink to train up. <p><IMG SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg" ></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uspiffatin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spiffatin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/7/01 10:13:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Yep</span><hr size=1> Grimstaff speaks truth... I spent 2.5k at the guildmaster's at 49 to get ice comet and supernova.<br>
